Description: Alita is a powerful cyborg with a soft heart and a mysterious past.
Title: BATTLE ANGEL ALITA: LAST ORDER, VOL. 17
Author: Yukito Kishiro

Description: From the publisher: "Naruto impresses the Allied Shinobi Forces with his newfound strength."
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 60
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: Yuma Tsukumo will stop at nothing to become the Duel Masters champion, but as a rank amateur, the odds are stacked against him. Luckily, he has a mysterious spirit named Astral to help him.
Title: YU-GI-OH! ZEXAL, VOL. 2
Author: Kazuki Takahashi

Description: Oz, who is condemned to an abyss for a mysterious sin, sets out to investigate his new world with Alice, an equally mysterious girl he met in exile.
Title: PANDORA HEARTS, VOL. 14
Author: Jun Mochizuki

Description: From the publisher: “Mochizuki General Hospital boasts some of the most well-trained (and well-endowed) nurses in town.” By day, they fight sickness. By night, they fight evil.
Title: TRIAGE X, VOL. 2
Author: Shouji Sato

Description: Yuki Sakuragi has the power to read the thoughts of anyone he touches. The power can be a burden and now he has met Zess, a beautiful stranger that is somehow familiar. What is afoot?
Title: THE BETRAYAL KNOWS MY NAME, VOL. 5
Author: Hotaru Odagiri

Description: High school misfits unite in “The Neighbors Club” in an attempt to better fit in. Will their classmates ever accept them?
Title: HAGANAI: I DON'T HAVE MANY FRIENDS, VOL. 2
Author: Yomi Hirasaka and Itachi

Description: A secluded mansion on an island + an inheritance up for grabs + a witch = a fight for survival.
Title: UMINEKO: WHEN THEY CRY — LEGEND OF THE GOLDEN WITCH, VOL. 2
Author: Ryukishi07 and Kei Natsumi

Description: Sailor Moon fights for justice in the name of the Moon and the mysterious Moon Princess. Along the way, she recruits other girls to be Sailor Scouts and join her fight against evil.
Title: SAILOR MOON, VOL. 9
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: Ichigo Kurosaki sees dead people and must help usher them safely into the afterlife. In this volume, people are disappearing and a dark shadow is heading toward Ichigo.
Title: BLEACH, VOL. 55
Author: Tite Kubo
